inn1.comm: starts good length, just outside off, Jamshed pats it back
another one on good length, similar line around off, Jamshed across to defend
pitched fuller now, superb line on off stump, blocked
fuller one again, towards middle now, knocked back to the bowler
sotly turns a length ball from just outside off to midwicket
beaten, similar to the delivery he got out to in the first game, slanted across for the drive, Jamshed reaches feebly for it
slants it across the right-hander, good length, spot-on with the line outside off, punched away
super delivery, Shehzad left it on the original line going across him, but it jagged back in from short of a length and bounced over the stumps
right on off stump, skiddy length ball, short of driving length, defended
short of a length but this time the line is on to the pad, and Shehzad's tickled it fine
walks across to a good length ball holding the line on middle and works it square to leg, but there is a man there in the ring
fuller, but he walks across again in the crease, and knocks it back to the bowler
pitched up just around off stump, Jamshed pushes it back to the bowler
fullish delivery again, and he uses the slight width to squeeze it in the gap past cover
comes forward this time, something he has not done a lot, and pushes firmly to mid off
solidly on to the front foot to block a length ball outside off
tries to score off this slightly widish one but knocks it straight to cover
stays on the crease now as he tries to work one from off to midwicket, can't time it
Vitori starts with one that holds the line but starts leg stump, and is tucked square
some away swing from the left-hander, Jamshed cannot time the cover drive as he steps forward
this is overpitched now, into the pads too, and Jamshed flicks it in the air behind square leg, too quick for the man at fine leg
tries to work it square again, but this is not as full, but they'll get the single as ball rolls close to the pitch
nice leave, this was close to off stump, holding the line too, but Shehzad's judgment was spot-on

oh dear, and next ball, he goes reaching for a widish, pitched up delivery and ends up spooning it weakly to shortish backward point, completely nothing shot in the end, that just popped to the fielder
forward to a pitched up ball to push to covers
Jamshed is moving forward neatly now, pushes to extra cover this time
leg stump line from just short of driving length, and easily tucked behind square
width on this length delivery and Jamshed carves it past point with an open face
slanted across widish, Jamshed not going for it
right on middle, good length, turned to midwicket
first ball, Hafeez flows into a crisp drive to an overpitched delivery, but the man at extra cover dives to keep him to one
just short of a length, tight line on off, blocked from the crease
Jamshed gets this length delivery into the gap to the left of mid on, taking it from outside off stump
superb timing now, as Jamshed leans forward and clips this length ball on middle and leg past midwicket's dive
nice comeback from the bowler, this length ball straightens just outside off, and is defended
sprays this length ball well down leg now, bounces in front of the keeper, but he has it covered with early movement
width from a length, but Jamshed does not attack it much, guides it to point
good length angled into the pad, but Hafeez cannot work it away
on the stumps, he is across to defend to the bowler
again the angle takes it into the pad, and this time Hafeez clips it through midwicket
pitched up on the off stump line, he comes forward to smother it
targetting the stumps again with a pitched up delivery, Hafeez defends quickly
taking a big stride forward to block, the ball drops onto the pitch off the bat and pad
widish length delivery to start off, across the left-hander, who gets too far across and cannot time the cut
short of a length, climbing outside off, Jamshed brings it down into the pitch
Jamshed is timing that clip through midwicket superbly today, didn't do that in the first game, takes it from around off and turns it past mid on, who chases and stops it with a slide inches inside
beaten, Hafeez was troubled with this delivery early in the first match as well, lifts from just short of driving length, angled in so he looks to play at it, whizzes past the outside edge
but the follow-up is overpitched into the pad, and Hafeez easily tucks it behind square
comes forward to a pitched up ball and defends to covers

he's tried to force this delivery through the off side, it wasn't exactly pitched up, he was dropped at second slip off a similar delivery first game, manages to mishit in the air between extra cover and mid off this time
length ball played out to mid on
good length, right on off stump, defended
single safely taken after some excited shouts from the fielders after a tuck in front of square leg
Zimbabwe have bowled a lot of deliveries on the pads today, another one is worked behind square
moves across in the crease and turns a length ball to shortish midwicket
sharp save by Sibanda jumping at short cover, Jamshed had driven this hard into the pitch and it was bouncing over the fielder
another wide, sent on a good length down leg
there is short cover, this is pitched up for the drive, and Jamshed has cracked it in the air, but wide of the man and it races through extra cover
Jamshed batting quite freely now, not much width on this back of a length ball but he ekes out a single with a mistimed cut behind point
good length outside off, Hafeez stays in the crease and runs it to third man
good length, just outside off, starting outside leg and angling across, defended with a shuffle and a straight bat
big shuffle across to push to the leg side
stays a tad low from a length just outside off stump, Hafeez adjusts to punch it to long off
tossed up on middle and leg, nudged off the front foot behind square for a quick single
length ball worked down to long on
swats a length delivery from off down to long on
forward to defend a tossed up ball around off
worked past midwicket to wide long on
there for the cut, short and wide, Hafeez slashes and the ball flies over the lone slip
a thick edge runs to third man as Hafeez plays back to a skiddy, bouncing length ball
comes neatly forward to run this pitched up ball wide of point for one more
pitched up wide for the drive, Hafeez takes a big step out and shoulders arms
lift from a good length now, Hafeez wisely lets it go once more

pitched up into off and middle, turned past midwicket, it is timed deceptively well, and almost reaches the rope before the chasing fielder manages to stop it, but Hafeez has called for the fourth by that time
knocked back in the air but out of the bowler's reach to his left, and down to long on
some spin now, but into the pad, and wristily turned to deep square
tossed up ball defended off the front foot
goes back  and across to a flighted ball with some turn, plays it to midwicket
pushed down the pitch
wants to cut, but this is close to off and does not turn, he mishits to cover
short of driving length, punched nicely to cover
full into the pads, he is lucky Hafeez's clip finds midwicket
bounce from a length, but too wide to interest Hafeez
another lifter, Hafeez walks across to off and pulls bat out of the way
defended off the front foot to extra cover
this came in from a good length, Hafeez had already left it, but again it started too far to cause damage

this looks straight and again, it is Utseya with the opening breakthrough, lots of flight from round the stumps, but it is the appreciable drift that does it for Jamshed as he is beaten on the forward push, pushes outside the line, and is struck in front of middle, the only doubt would have to be the height as he was hit on the knee roll, and the ball had quite some distance to cover
stretches right forward to smother it
opens up and punches hard but bowler cuts it off to his right
crouches forward and pushes softly towards point
Misbah tries an early reverse paddle, does not get it past short third
opens the face and guides it behind point
Chatara remains good length outside off to Hafeez, who keeps letting them go
too wide this time and Hafeez attacks it, but mishits it to short extra off the toe end
good length, widish, left alone
Hafeez walks down now, looking to put Chatara off his line, but bowler remains good length outside off, and Hafeez has to let it go once more
bangs it in short, and sprays it too far outside off
an outside edge, but Hafeez has played it softly, dropping his wrists as he stretches forward and keeping it down past gully, needs a diving effort at third man
guided square but point dives to prevent the single
bat in front of pad as he pushes forward to midwicket
reaches forward again and nudges square on the leg side
moves across and pats a length ball away
flighted across from round the stumps, defended down the track
caught in the crease as he moves across, this one spins in sharply, possibly going down leg
Hafeez on the walk to Chatara again, he's been tied down by this good length outside off, pushes and sets off, but cover is onto the ball
angled in from wide of the crease, comes in further after pitching, Hafeez lets it go
another one moves in after pitching good length outside off, Hafeez takes a stride out and leaves
again Hafeez leaves the crease and walks outside off but Chatara does well to stick to the same line, one more leave
Hafeez is already well down the pitch when this arrives good length outside off, chooses to shoulder arms yet again
has to play this time, this is much closer to off, good length, Hafeez defends off the front foot
Misbah tries the reverse sweep from the leg stump line to a tossed up ball, but finds short third man
cramped for room as he goes back and forces it to the bowler
Misbah is off the mark, gets one down the pads and works it square
staying a tad low outside off, punched to extra cover
Hafeez takes on Utseya now, he did this pretty early in his innings in the first game, charges out and lofts cleanly straight over the bowler and out of long on's reach
chance for a run out, Hafeez rushes for the single after a confident push wide of point, but is sent back and just makes it in time as the throw arrives to the keeper
nice, Misbah is searching for this one close to off as it angles across and moves away slightly to beat him
a big stride forward to defend a length ball to the leg side now
good length, right on off, blocked
beaten again, slight away movement taking it further away on the angle as Misbah is opened up and pokes
too far across with all the angle at work and chop-guides it to point
Misbah is having a hard time out there, ducks into a shortish ball now and is hit on the back, near the left shoulder
flat and quick on a good length, punched to long on
forward to defend a slowly tossed up ball, it rolls onto the crease

chance gone at deep backward square leg, Vitori hesitates too much in running forward to this top-edged sweep, and by the time he decided to go for the catch, it is already dipping and pings his hands to roll away, was in the air for a long time, should have been taken quite comfortably really
defended off the front foot
Hafeez rubs it in with a waltz down the pitch and a massive blow high over long on
bounce from back of a length hits the bat high, they take the quick single in front of point
good length on the pads, tucked to deep backward square

Misbah's slow start has consumed him today, he'd allowed himself to be tied down and decided to resort to a big walk across to turn this length delivery past midwicket, ended up chipping it in the air, and the man there took a sharp catch to his left
length ball defended towards point
lovely, straightens it outside off and gets it to lift from short of a length, Amin is beaten as he prods off the back foot
a short ball now, around off stump, Amin drops the wrists withdraws inside the line
length ball holding the line on off, defended
some late away shape widish outside off, Hafeez beaten as he checks his drive
pitched up around off, he reaches forward to squeeze it to mid off
sprays it way down the leg side, keeper is standing up, and has no chance
beaten on the cut now off a widish length ball, extra bounce does it
manages to get bat on this one and beats point's dive, sweeper runs around to stop it
starts alright with a sharp length ball on the stumps, which is defended
oversteps as he pitches it outside leg and slants it across the left-hander slightly, the ball goes behind point off the pad
Hafeez makes full use of the free hit, sets himself up for the mow over midwicket, gets a length ball on off, and makes a clean connection
pitched up and angled in, he leans forward to work it to long on
worked out to deep square leg
full into middle and leg, away to short fine leg
squeezes an overpitched ball to extra cover
pitched up, angled across, driven off the front foot to extra cover
held the line on leg stump from a length, Amin got the bat around just in time
pitched just outside leg stump, as replays show, before pinging him on the pad from a good length, going down leg too probably
pushed to extra cover for a quick single
overpitched, pushed to deepish mid off
guides a widish length ball past point, sweeper gets to it quickly and keeps them to one
full from over the stumps, knocked down to long off, and this is another fifty for Hafeez
full on middle and leg, hit to long on
misfield by the bowler at short midwicket allows the single
full all the time, Amin eases it to wide long off
he plays back to a fullish delivery, and is hit on the pad, that was dead in front, but the ball pitched outside leg
pushed to covers
pitched up ball driven to mid off
pitched up again, around off, he mishits a drive to extra cover
full and wide, eased out to the sweeper
overpitched again, and Hafeez makes him pay this time, finding the gap with a drive past extra cover, mid off has no chance in the chase
knocks a length ball down the track and calls early for the single, mid off runs around
flashed hard in the air but past backward point, third man cuts it off
pitches outside leg from over the wicket and is nudged square
bat in front of pad to work to midwicket
tossed up full down the pad, turned to deep square
on off stump, Amin defends close to the pitch
appears to come down the track, does not, Williams sends it down the leg side
mistimes a forcing stroke for the bowler to dive to his right and stop it
excellent save at fine leg with a sprawling dive, else this sweep was headed into the rope
not that short, it is almost good length really, but Hafeez has picked it quickly and powerfully over midwicket
defends a loopy slower one off the front foot
jabs a length ball past point, and races back for the second as third man runs around
leans forward, bat in front of pad, to turn it square on the leg side
right on off stump, good length, pushed back
straightening delivery flicked to midwicket, who almost catches Hafeez short of his ground at the non-striker's, but the throw misses
tossed up offspinner punched to covers
full, eased to long on off the front foot
thick edge as he pushes to a tossed up ball, which runs to short third man
hurries in with the angle, he chops it hard, it eludes a jumping extra cover
allows it to spin in from outside off and works it in front of square leg, wide enough of deep midwicket to take two
sharp spin now towards off stump, Hafeez backs away for the cut but it arrives quickly and he cannot beat point
appeal for catch down the leg side, didn't seem to be bat as Amin tried to flick it
flowing into the drive, holding the followthrough, but finding extra cover
sprays it full and wide outside off, called one, was just inside the marker
checks the drive to a pitched up ball and gets it to the left of midoff

just back of a length, pushed to point, Amin is more than half way up the pitch, there is no single here, Amin has to turn back, he dives in, and also manages to elude a jumping midwicket running in, but the throw was quite off target
just outside off stump, hits the bat hard as Hafeez pushes to covers
starts with a pitched up ball on off stump, which is patted back
overpitched onto the pads, flicked in front of square leg, but not wide enough of the deep fielder to return for the second
not far from off stump, pushed softly in front of point for one
into the pads to the left-hander again, back of a length now, rolls away behind square
this has surprised him, but there is no one at square leg, bouncer gets big on Hafeez, he looks to avoid it late, but it hits the bat close to the splice, and loops square
length ball clipped neatly through midwicket, Vitori has had issues adjusting to the left-hander in this over
overpitched ball turned to a diving midwicket
length ball on off punched to long on
overpitched down the pad, turned past midwicket, Hafeez wants the second, Amin does not
comes down and works it to midwicket
angled in from over the wicket and he turns it to midwicket again
finds short fine leg this time as he works off the pad
outside off, struck on the pads, futile appeal for lbw
flatter on the leg stump, steered to fine leg
tossed up on off, driven down the ground to long-off for a single
slightly slower on middle, tucked to square leg with the turn
straight ball on middle, pushed to midwicket
flighted and Amin comes down and drives it to long-off
flighted on off, driven back to the bowler
slightly short, Amin goes back and tries to pull but misses it completely
quicker one on the stumps, defended in the crease
flighted on middle, Amin drives it down the ground to long-on
flat and on length outside off, defended after the turn
slightly shorter on off, Hafeez turns it square on the leg side off the back foot and they come back for two
flighted outside off from round the stumps and Amin comes down and drives it between midwicket and mid-on for four
four on the off side this time! It pitched on middle and Amin came down, made room and played it inside out over covers for four. Nobody in the deep
length ball on off, cut off the back foot to point
flatter one well outside off, left alone easily
outside off again, Amin comes down again but edges it to short third man
full on off, Amin pushes it to point with soft hands
length ball on the pads, turned to the left of mid-on for a single
length ball angled in towards the pads, steered to short fine leg
length ball on middle and off, pushed down to long-off
banged in short of length, Hafeez goes back a bit and pushes it to point
short of length, Amin whips it on the back foot to deep square leg
length ball angled in to the pads, Hafeez steers it fine on the leg side wide of short fine leg for four
right in the block hole on middle, defended by Amin
length ball on off, driven straight to cover
short of length on off, Amin goes back and turns it towards midwicket
shot ball on leg and Hafeez pulls it away for four to the fine leg boundary by turning on his heel
slower ball going down leg and Hafeez tucks it to short fine leg for a single
length ball just outside off, Amin tries to run it down fine but misses it
slower ball outside off, driven to cover
full and outside off, Hafeez can't pierce the gap in the covers again
short and wide outside off, Hafeez can't time it right this time and cuts it to extra cover
in the block hole on off, defended on off and they take a single
full and well outside off, Amin leans forward and slams it absolutely straight over the bowler for a six
short and outside off, Amin stays back and cuts it past point for four. Another productive over for Pakistan
yorker on the stumps, defended on off
full on off, Hafeez takes a step forward and whips it past midwicket for a single
full and wide outside off, Amin drives it over point for another four. He's finding the gaps pretty easily now
overpitched on off, driven down to long-off
another full delivery, driven down straight pretty easily by Hafeez
full again, driven by Amin on off and the fielder throws it back quickly but Amin has made his ground for his first fifty
outside leg and goes down further for a wide
short of length outside off, cut to sweeper cover off the back foot
short of length on middle, turned to deep square leg and the call is for two but Amin slips while turning for the second and it's only a single
short and wide but struck straight to cover
full outside off, driven down to long-off
short of length outside off, Hafeez runs it down fine to third man and Masakadza dives to his lef just inside the boundary to save two
on the pads, Hafeez turns it to log and it takes a leading edge but falls well short of the fielder at long-on
on length outside off, Hafeez cuts it after the turn for a single
slightly slower on the stumps, Amin comes down and lofts it over the infield on the leg side for a couple
lenght ball outside off, Amin comes down again and cuts it on off. It's gone behind square for a four
length ball on off, driven to cover and Hafeez is sent back for a single
flighted and short of length outside off, cut to sweeper cover for a single
slower and outside off, Hafeez has merely driven it through the covers and it's gone for four. He didn't go hard at it but the timing made sure it went all the way and beat long-off
full on the pads, Amin tries to whip it away but is crammed up for room
low full toss on middle, driven back to the bowler
short and outside leg, wide given by the umpire

almost in the block hole outside off, Amin pushes it on the on side and calls for a single but Chatara gets to it quickly and has a direct hit. Umar Amin's dive couldn't save him there as he was sent back by Hafeez
very short and well outside off, Afridi lets it go and he signals wide too, and the umpire follows
low and slow full toss on off, turned to the leg side for a single
short of length on off, turned to short midwicket
short of length well outside off, but just inside the line and Hafeez lets it go. Only three of the over
wide down the leg side
pitched outside off, Afridi tries to sweep but gets a leg bye on the off side
short on off, Hafeez goes back and cuts to cover where a misfield gives him three and Hafeez gets to his sixth ODI hundred. Takes his helmet off and acknowledges the applause
full on off, smashed back to the bowler and his foot saves some runs
full on leg, drive to long-on
short and wide, Hafeez cuts it straight to short third man
full on off, driven down to long-off for a single
slow and full on off, turned on the leg side. Call was for two but the fielder did well to cut it down to one
full on off, almost in the block hole, driven back to the bowler
slow short ball just outside off, Afridi pulls hard with all his might and misses it completely
full and wide, Afridi swings his arms and lofts it over the infield for four, nobody in the deep on the off side
full and wide again, Afridi swings again as he has enough room and he goes all the way over cover. Afridi in double figures
full on the pads, turned past midwicket for two
full toss outside off, Hafeez puts his front foot out and turns it square on the leg side
low full toss and driven down the ground for a single
short of length on the pads and he tucks it past midwicket for two
full on the pads, Hafeez has whipped it away just behind square on the leg side for four. Great timing
short of length on the leg stump, steered to short fine leg
full on the pads, Afridi turns it backward square leg for a single to keep the strike
low full toss on middle, chipped down to long-on for a single
full on the stumps, Hafeez has hit it straight down the ground in the air and it's gone just over long-on. The fielder got  a hand to it after jumping but couldn't hold on it and fell over the rope
full on off, drive to extra cover for a single
full and down the leg stump for a wide
almost in the block hole on middle, Afridi makes room and drives it to long-off

full on the pads and Hafeez has whipped it in the air towards deep square leg where the fielder in the deep jumps, catches it and throws it back inside the rope while falling over but he has touched the boundary and it's a six
slower and shorter on the stumps, Hafeez turns it to short fine leg
low full toss outside off, driven to cover for a single
slower ball on off, Afridi waits for it and pushes it to point
well down the leg side and Hafeez helps it over the short fine leg fielder to get four more
low full toss on middle, turned to deep square leg for a single
Afridi makes room and Vitori pitches it close to his leg and it's turned to the leg side again for a single
it pitched outside leg and went down further quickly beating both the batsman and the keeper all the way to the boundary
full on the pads, steered to deep fine leg for a single
full outside off, driven in the air to long-off after a bounce
targets the block hole and Afridi makes a bit of room and whips it to deep midwicket
right in the block hole, Hafeez defends and the ball is right next to him and they sneak a quick single
full delivery, Afridi paddles it from around off to short fine leg
in the block hole again, defended to point for a single
attempted yorker turns into a full toss and Afridi makes room to hoist it straight down the ground for a six. It was in the zone and he struck it with enough power to help it over the rope
full on middle, driven to long-on
low full toss on leg and it's driven to the right of long-off for two
waist high full toss, slapped over the bowler to long-on and Hafeez pushes Afridi for two
another full toss and Afridi has made room to go over the cover to launch it all th way over sweeper cover for six
short ball angled into the pads, Afridi fails to connect this time
low full toss on the stumps, Afridi makes room again and drives it to extra cover for a single. They can't reach 300, but that's what Zimbabwe will be chasing here today

inn2.comm: troubles him first ball, almost sneaks it through as it straightens into the right-hander very late, Masakadza manages a thick inside edge on the drive, the ball goes to fine leg
now a long shout for lbw, but this length ball pitched outside leg stump
it slips down leg as a high full toss, keeper has to dive
just back of a length, hits the defensive bat hard
banged in shortish, tickled down to fine leg
this is sharp stuff, short ball again, and this time it pings Sibanda on the glove before looping behind square leg
after all those short balls, he hurls in a yorker on the stumps, Masakadza falls onto the pitch but he's managed to dig it out to mid on, what an over
angled in to the pad and carries down leg, there is an appeal for caught behind, looked to be the pad
fuller, middle and leg, knocked down to long on
fast, flat, outside off, punched to covers
hit on the pad on the forward push as this arm ball carries in, but sliding down leg
pushes froward down to deep mid on, but they don't take the single, queer
almost through, almost, straightens on the stumps and skids on fast, but Masakadza's managed an inside edge before it took the pad
short of a length, middle and off, pushed to leg close to the pitch
first man down, Irfan's short balls have been really quick, Sibanda's tried his favoured pull, but the top-edge has swirled high and straight, and keeper is right under as it comes down
plays inside the line of a short of a length ball angled across
drops the wrists on another lifter slanted past him
turns a back of a length ball to midwicket
serious examination this, short, at the batsman, who fends it down the pitch, lucky it did not carry to the advancing bowler
straightening on off stump, blocked off the front foot
goes for the reverse sweep to a ball on off but cannot beat backward point
he tries the shot once more and this time runs it to the vacant third man rope
nice, Rehman tosses it up for once, Taylor pushes forward, moves a touch inside the line, and lofts cleanly over mid off
darted into the pad, worked square, they take two by the time Irfan runs around from fine leg
drives a fullish ball to long off, who's been sent back after that boundary
very full outside off stump, he reaches for it but cannot connect
full delivery pushed wide of mid off, the throw is wide, but they decide against running again
Sibanda fell on the pull, now Masakadza tries it, picking it neatly in the air and in front of square leg, this one didn't bounce as much
backs away to leg and tries to force a short ball over the off side, Irfan has overstepped
Irfan tries to go for the yorker, does not get it right, Masakadza hangs back and clubs it in the air, straight down the ground
quick single taken with a dab to a length ball behind point
hops and brings down a lifter onto the pitch
good length ball right on off stump, defended to the off side, no single coming
slight width and he pounces on it, but the cut is straight on the bounce to backward point
good length on off stump, pushed to extra cover
length ball placed wide of cover, Amin dives and stops the ball, but they have time to take a single
punches a short of a length ball to midwicket
stays back to a length ball outside off and pushes to mid off
punches a short of a length ball hard, but straight to mid off
short of a length again, widish too, he fairly thumps it, in the air and on the bounce, again to mid off
tries to dab a short ball past the keeper, misses
he's picked the gap this time, he's been trying to hit it to the left of mid off, made some room outside leg stump and forced a length ball in that area this time
overpitched, and no need to back away to leg as Masakadza takes a step forward and powers it through extra cover
shifts the line to middle stump, slows it down as well, Masakadza blocks
moves across and defends onto the crease, tries to sneak a single, but Junaid is quick to the ball
one hand comes off the bat as he mistimes a drive to cover off a length ball
middle and leg, and worked behind square leg, they think about the second, but deep square has cut off that possibility with a sprint and quick, accurate throw
dismissed down the ground, overpitched delivery, Masakadza cranks up and gives it a nice thump

right through him, Junaid is pumped up, off stump is uprooted, Masakadza's tried to force one too many, was caught on the crease this time to a good length ball and was in an awkward position to play the punch down the ground, missed, and Junaid hit the top of off
goes across in the crease to a length ball around off and keeps it out
goes across and pushes a short of a length ball to short cover
Taylor was in big trouble had extra cover, running across, picked up this ball, he did what he could, dived in
slanted quick and widish across the right-hander, steep bounce
very full on the pad, nudged to square leg
rolls off the pad down leg, they decide to take the run late, but pull through safely in the end
back of a length, he is across and on his toes to punch to mid off
neat drive as he leans onto the front foot but there is a man at short extra cover, right in the way
shortish and wide, there for the cut, but he misses
pushes a length ball on middle to the bowler
on off stump now, pitched up, blocked

sharp, accurate bouncer, Maruma was hoping he would avoid it, but it kept climbing at him, and he's just managed to crouch inches under it, falls down on the pitch with the effort and smiles at the bowler
length ball angled across close to off, and it's a very confident leave
tossed up outside off, nudged to midwicket
overpitched, whipped down to longon
length ball goes straight outside off, jabbed back
goes across to off to defend a length ball
drives an overpitched ball and Hafeez cannot stop it to his right with his foot, away to long on
Taylor slithers out and plays a smooth, clean loft high over the bowler
defends a length ball towards short extra cover and sets off, but there is no single here
yorker, kept out, just, loops up and falls onto the crease, could have gone anywhere
huge appeal for leg before but that was clearly pitching well outside leg stump, more than a foot outside
blocks to the leg side and even as they think of one, Junaid races to the ball
appeal for caught behind turned down, Junaid dug in the short ball around off, Taylor crouched and tried to run it over slip late, but missed
full delivery driven for point to make a diving stop
sees him coming out and darts it in full, Maruma knocks it down to long on
tosses it up around off, pushed away
nudged through square leg, Jamshed is confused whether to go for the ball from the infield, sees the man from the deep is too deep and gets on with the job in the end
pushes forward, the ball takes inside edge and pops up square on the leg side, safely
overpitched ball forced down to long on
nice, firm drive off the front foot but he's picked mid off
full on the pad, and tucked through midwicket for a couple
bouncer, right on target, Maruma sways inside the line early
cramped for room with one holding the line on middle and leg, they take the single as it rolls away to leg close to the wicket
length ball pushed to midwicket, Junaid runs after it, had he picked it up, the single would have been much tighter
goes for the yorker, not quite full, dug out
spins in from outside off, nudged square to leg
forces a length ball straight back to the bowler
going too hard at the ball, gets this one down to long on
gets bat around front pad to turn it to deep square leg
goes straight one from a length, he swats it back to the bowler

Maruma's run himself out, really no single here, but he'd not been scoring much, pushed towards extra cover and set off, the man ran in, picked it up, and lobbed it to the keeper, Taylor sent Maruma back, but he had too much ground to recover
length ball on off, defended to short third man
short of length on leg, turned away behind square on leg
shot of length on off, Williams steers it to fine leg after the run
length ball on middle and leg, tucked on the leg side for a quick single
quicker one outside off, pushed to cover
flighted delivery on length, Williams tries to turn it past midwicket but the fielder dives to his right to stop the single
length ball on off, reverse swept square of the wicket for a four. There are two fielders behind square but he kept it away from them by a distance
on length on off, pushed down to long-on
length ball outside off, driven past through the covers for a single
slower on length on off, turned to midwicket. They considered a second but it would have led to another run out
flatter on middle, pushed down to mid-on
fuller on middle, defended on the off side
with some flight on middle, Taylor turns it to short fine leg and rightly send s Williams back for the single
on middle again, turned square on leg for a single
flighted on off, tucked to midwicket
shorter and quicker, driven to cover
flighted on off, swept to deep fine leg for a single
length ball on the pads, turned to midwicket for a single
length ball outside off, defended on the leg side, it kept a little low
round the wicket, Williams turns a full ball to mid-on for a quick single
flighted and full on off, Taylor turns it to deep fine leg
short of length on off, Williams comes down and drives to long-off
short of length on off, Taylor pushes it down on the leg side and midwicket runs to his left to stop the single
similar delivery, but slightly wider on off, driven down to long-on
short of length outside off, driven to sweeper cover with ease
short of length wide of off, swept without follow through to fine leg by Williams
length ball on middle, defended back to Rehman
flighted on the leg stump, driven down to long-on
flighted outside off on length, Williams charges down and manages it over the infield over cover for two
full on off, swept to deep square leg for a single
short ball outside off, Williams is using his feet very well as he has whipped this one past midwicket and deep square leg for four
fuller on off, defended back to the bowler
full and just outside off, driven to long-off
short of length on middle and leg, steered to backward square leg
short and wuick on off, punched on the leg side for a single
length ball on off, defended on the leg side
short of length on middle, turned down to short fine leg
length ball on off, defended back to the bowler
flighted outside off, Williams comes down and a fumble at mid-offgives them a single
flighted on off and Taylor has just chipped it inside out over cover for four, fielder in the deep can't get there on time
shorter and quicker on leg, steered to backward square leg
short and flat outside off, Williams sweeps and misses. Stifled lbw appeal as it struck him outside off
full on off, turned on the leg side behind square
round the stumps, full on off and defended by Williams
full on middle, Williams slogs it over midwicket but the turn takes a thick edge fine on the off side, past short third man, for four

length ball on middle, Williams has got it over short third man this time. The reverse swep got a top edge and went well over the fielder in the circle. He's trying to unsettle Ajmal in his first over
full and flighted on off, turned to the cow corner for a single
slow and on length on off, Taylor has turned it on the leg side for a single and brings up his fifty. It will do his confidence some good after a lean patch until the last match
full on middle, driven to midwicket
quicker one on length on middle and leg, turned square of midwicket
round the wicket, short of length leg spinner outside off and Williams chipped it towards long-on and it fell well short
length ball on the stumps, defended on the leg side
full on leg, turned towards square leg
short of length well outside off, Williams waits for the turn and guides it to fine leg off the back foot with a straight bat
length ball on off, defended on leg side
Williams comes down to convert this into a half volley and drives it to deep midwicket for two
on length on leg stump, turned to midwicket for a single
short and flat on middle and leg, pushed to square leg
slightly quicker outside off, Williams sweeps and misses
flighted and low full toss outside off, driven straight to point
the wrong one outside off, defended on off itself
slightly more flighted and it's gone high up in the air and dropped! Taylor sort of slogged it on the leg side against the turn and Ajmal made a mess of it
full on off, driven down the ground
full on off and Taylor comes forward and drives it over cover for four. He's not scared to take the aerial route
full on middle, turned to square leg
full and flighted and Williams has driven it straight down the ground for a four. He took the aerial route and there was nobody in the deep as mid-off was in
full on off, driven to cover
length ball on leg, turned to short fine leg. Williams comes down a long away and is denied the single
length ball outside off, pushed past extra cover
full on off and Williams reverse sweeps. It took the top edge and went well over short third man for a couple
full on off, pushed back to Ajmal

short of length and quicker on middle, Williams comes down to turn it on the leg side but misses it completely and he is stumped easily by Sarfraz. He was finding the gaps and taking the aerial route pretty well, big wicket for Pakistan
oh dear, it was flat on off and he defended it but the turn almost got the outside edge
full on the pads, turned down to short fine leg
full outside off, driven straight to cover
short of length and quicker on off, defended back to Afridi
the wron' one outside off, defended after the turn
quicker and flatter down leg, that's a wide
flighted and full outside off, chipper over the covers for a single
length ball outside off, defended square of the wicket
short of length on off, it doesn't turn and he punched it through the covers for four, very well timed to find the gap
length ball on off, turned to midwicket
full on leg, turned on the leg side again
short of length on leg, turned square on the leg side off the back foot for a single
full on off and Waller has driven it down the ground, between Taylor's legs, for four. Mid-off is in the circle and the ball beat him by a distance
length ball outside off, defended to extra cover
shorter on off, pushed back to Afridi
another inside out drive over but they don't get four this time. Rehman ran all the way from sweeper cover to deep cover and threw himself to his right to save two
full on off, driven down to long-off
short of length, driven to point
quicker one going down leg side and he's got it past short fine leg for four
short of length on middle, turned to backward square leg
full outside off, defended to extra cover
short of length on off, turned to the leg side
shorter and quicker on off, Waller gets it behind square on the leg side
length ball on off, turned to midwicket
full on off, pushed to extra cover for a single
full delivery on middle, steered to backward square leg
length and quicker one that comes inside, the batsman misses it and there's a loud appeal for lbw. It pitched on off and turned but might be going down leg
on length outside off, cut to extra cover
short and wide, Waller cuts it between point and short third man for four, found the gap very well, without much footwork though
slower one outside off, defended on off for a quick single
short of length on off, pushed towards mid-on and a single by the time midwicket gets there
length ball on middle, defended by Taylor
length ball outside off, turns away and Taylor gets a thick inside edge to point
length ball on off, pushed back to Rehman
short of length outside off, Taylor drives it slightly wide of cover for a single
slower and outside off on length, Waller defended and the turn beat him
full on off, driven to cover where the fielder stop the single. Just a single from the over
length ball outside off, driven towards cover and a late call also gets them a single
quicker and on length outside off, Waller prods without footwork and misses
fuller outside off, Waller drives it to the left of third man for two
length ball on off, defended to point, though he as trying to run it to third man
full toss that goes straight down leg for a wide
length ball on middle, pushed to cover
length ball outside off, pushed past extra cover with soft hands
on length on off, defended towards cover
quicker one just outside off, Waller made some room to cut it fine but missed
short of length on middle, it was going pretty straight and hit the batsman on the knee roll. Loud appeal from Rehman turned down
short of length on off, turned down to long-on
fuller on middle and leg, driven down to long-on
short and flat outside off, Waller cuts and manages an inside edge onto his pads
length delivery outside off, pushed to cover for a single
shorter and outside off, Waller cuts it late to steer it to the right of Jamshed at third man
this one was closer to Waller, short of length, he wanted to run it down third man but an outside edge went just past the keeper for four. No footwork there
length ball on middle and leg, defended back to Irfan
length ball on middle, defended straight to point
on length on the pads, Waller tries to run it fine but manages a leg bye
full on off from round the stumps and Waller has lofted it straight down the ground for four. Mid-off is up and he cleared the fielder easily
pitches on leg, hits him on the pad and Ajmal appeals for lbw but they sneak a leg bye
on the pads, swept to short fine leg

pitches outside leg, swept straight to short fine leg and Taylor called for it straightaway. The decision for run-out has gone up and seems like Taylor's dive has saved him. Direct hit might have had him in trouble
full outside off, Taylor reverse sweeps and misses
full on the pads, Taylor tries to steer it square but misses
length ball on off, Waller jabs again without footwork and the late swing beats him again
slightly fuller on off, Waller pushes it to off but an inside edge on the pads gives him a single
length ball on middle and leg, pushed down straight for a single
length ball on the pads, pushed down towards long-on and Irfan could have stopped that but he didn't stretch properly
in the block hole and Irfan appeals for lbw but it struck him outside leg
it was full outside off and gave Waller enough room to swing his arms and loft it over cover for four. It came from the middle and beat everyone
length ball on middle, turned to short fine leg
length ball on middle, Waller goes back and pushes it to midwicket
length ball on leg, Waller goes towards off and steers it past midwicket
Taylor got into position to reverse sweep but Ajmal pitched it down the leg side, but it won't be a wide as he changed his stance
full on middle, with some turn and it hits him on the pads. A lone appeal from Ajmal gets only a smile form the umpire

on length on middle, Taylor swept it and the leading edge would have gone well over the short fine leg fielder. But, it's Mohammad Irfan, who goes back a couple of steps and sticks his left hand out to take it easily. The big man catches the big fish

played on and two in two for Pakistan. It was a length ball on off and going away, Waller prods without footwork and the inside edge heads to the stumps. The umpires are checking for a no-ball and Junaid's heel is slightly inside the crease. Two big blows might have ended the chase for Zimbabwe
in the block hole outside off, Utseya gets bat to it but starts a little late for the single and a direct hit at non-striker's end might have had him run out

big appeal for lbw and he's given. It hit him in front of the pads for sure after pitching on length but the umpire has made a mistake here as it pitched well outside leg, wasn't even marginal. Chigumbura tried to steer it on the on side, but has to walk back after a rough decision
in the block hole again outside off, Panyangara gets an inside edge which misses the stumps and goes to the left of the keeper
length ball well outside off, he swings and misses without any footwork
length ball hits him on the pads and Junaid appeals loudly again but it's turned down this time. It was going down leg and it pitched outside leg
short of length outside off, pushed to cover
full on the pads, turned to square leg for a single
length ball angled into the stumps, defended towards extra cover
length ball on middle, defended back towards Rehman
lon length on the leg stump, Panyangara goes back and defends
short of length on the stumps, Panyangara misses while trying to steer it to leg but misses and they sneak a leg bye
full on middle and off, goes hard at it by making room but manages an edge towards midwicket
bouncer on the leg stump, Utseya pulls it in time for a single
full on off, another inside edge and another single as it goes to short fine leg

inside edge gets him this time. The change of angle might have done it here as it pitched on length and was going towards off but the inside edge sends the legs stump for a walk. The other bail - on off and middle - doesn't budge at all
low full toss outside off, driven on the off side
full delivery is driven down to mid-off where Irfan bends and sends it back flat to the bowler's end while they sneak a single
flighted on middle and leg, swept to deep fine leg
full on the pads and swept towards deep midwicket. Umar Amin was coming in plunged forward but couldn't get there in time to catch it, wasn't an easy catch
the keeper takes it now! It was short and outside off, Chatara tried to cut after it turned and an edge only found Sarfraz Ahmed's gloves

flighted outside off on length, Vitori swept it with a big stride and a leading edge goes high up in the air behind the keeper. Irfan runs to his right from short third man and takes a good catch. All over for Zimbabwe
